# 4. Understanding the Substitute Command

Example:

```bash
sed 's/Linux/Unix/' file.txt
```

Breakdown:

```text
s/Linux/Unix/

s
↓
Substitute

Linux
↓
Search pattern

Unix
↓
Replacement text
```

General format:

```text
s/search/replacement/
```

