```

---

# 13. Print the Last Line

Use:

```bash
sed -n '$p' employees.txt
```

Here:

```text
$
```

means:

```text
Last line
```

---

# 14. Print from a Line Number to the End

Example:

```bash
sed -n '5,$p' employees.txt
```

This prints:

```text
Line 5
through
Last line
```

