# 🧑‍💻 PSA Real-Time Scenario 4 – Extract an Incident Time Window

Suppose the log has clear markers:

```text
INCIDENT_START
...
INCIDENT_END
```

Use:

```bash
sed -n '/INCIDENT_START/,/INCIDENT_END/p' application.log
```

This prints the complete range.

If the end marker is missing, the output may continue to the end of the file.

Always understand the data structure before using pattern ranges.

